{"title_page": "Colive", "text_new": "'''Colive ''' is an Indian company that provides  technology-equipped fully managed rental [[Coliving|co-living space]] to students, working professionals and couples.They currently operate in [[Hyderabad]], [[Chennai]], [[Pune]] and Bengaluru and has its headquarters in Bengaluru, Karnataka.<ref>{{cite news |last1=S.H |first1=Salman |title=CoLive raises Rs12 crore from SAR Group and others |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/9UVfSwrzTjXx7ja1SXKgYP/CoLive-raises-Rs12-crore-from-SAR-Group-and-others.html |work=Livemint |date=23 February 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=News  |first1=ANI |title=Co-living space provider CoLive raises Rs.12 crore towards expansion |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coliving-space-provider-colive-raises-rs12-crore-towards-expansion/1258639 | |issue=22 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThis company was founded in the year 2016 by Suresh Rangarajan to provide shared living space to migrant students and professionals who look for readily available furnished homes or appartments  with modern amenities in Urban areas. This company was started in February 2016 in [[Vellore]] and [[Coimbatore]] with the Initial finance of Rs 12 Crores which they received from a Family Office.In 2019 they partnered with [[Salarpuria Sattva|Salarpuria Sattva Group]] by receiving $9.2 million as venture capital finance. This company is managing the inventory of 20,000 beds in [[Chennai]], [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]], and [[Hyderabad]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=S.H |first1=Salman |title=CoLive raises Rs12 crore from SAR Group and others |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/9UVfSwrzTjXx7ja1SXKgYP/CoLive-raises-Rs12-crore-from-SAR-Group-and-others.html |work=Livemint |date=23 February 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Adlakha |first1=Nidhi |title=The era of co-living |url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/homes-and-gardens/why-the-co-living-segment-is-trending/article26675229.ece |work=The Hindu |date=29 March 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first1= |title=4 platforms ensuring women's safety with tech-based solutions |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/technology/in-other-news/270120/4-platforms-ensuring-womens-safety-with-tech-based-solutions.html |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=27 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Reference==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Indian companies established in 2016]]\n[[Category:Real estate companies of India]]\n", "text_old": "'''Colive ''' is an Indian company that provides  technology-equipped fully managed rental [[Coliving|co-living space]] to students, working professionals and couples.They currently operate in [[Hyderabad]], [[Chennai]], [[Pune]] and Bengaluru and has its headquarters in Bengaluru Karnataka.<ref>{{cite news |last1=S.H |first1=Salman |title=CoLive raises Rs12 crore from SAR Group and others |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/9UVfSwrzTjXx7ja1SXKgYP/CoLive-raises-Rs12-crore-from-SAR-Group-and-others.html |work=Livemint |date=23 February 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=News  |first1=ANI |title=Co-living space provider CoLive raises Rs.12 crore towards expansion |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coliving-space-provider-colive-raises-rs12-crore-towards-expansion/1258639 | |issue=22 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThis company was founded in the year 2016 by Suresh Rangarajan to provide shared living space to migrant students and professionals who look for readily available furnished homes or appartments  with modern amenities in Urban areas. This company was started in February 2016 in [[Vellore]] and [[Coimbatore]] with the Initial finance of Rs 12 Crores which they received from a Family Office.In 2019 they partnered with [[Salarpuria Sattva|Salarpuria Sattva Group]] by receiving $9.2 million as venture capital finance. This company is managing the inventory of 20,000 beds in [[Chennai]], [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]], and [[Hyderabad]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=S.H |first1=Salman |title=CoLive raises Rs12 crore from SAR Group and others |url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/9UVfSwrzTjXx7ja1SXKgYP/CoLive-raises-Rs12-crore-from-SAR-Group-and-others.html |work=Livemint |date=23 February 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Adlakha |first1=Nidhi |title=The era of co-living |url=https://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/homes-and-gardens/why-the-co-living-segment-is-trending/article26675229.ece |work=The Hindu |date=29 March 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first1= |title=4 platforms ensuring women's safety with tech-based solutions |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/technology/in-other-news/270120/4-platforms-ensuring-womens-safety-with-tech-based-solutions.html |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=27 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Reference==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Indian companies established in 2016]]\n[[Category:Real estate companies of India]]\n", "name_user": "Sagotreespirit", "label": "safe", "comment": "Comma", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colive"}
